defaultWe own and manage over
default 28,000 homes across London and the South East of England. We focus on core social housing activities offe
defaultring a range of housing options. 
defaultA
defaultHL
default also 
defaultprovides 1,150 private rented sector (PRS) homes for use 
defaultas temporary accommodation (TA).
default We manage these homes through a trading entity called Avenue Lettings. We lease homes from 500 individual landlords and work with 18 local authorities
default (LA
default) 
defaultto
default provide great quality self contained homes for homeless families.  We’ve been providing this ser
defaultvice for over 11 years. 
default&#xa0;
defaultAHL support the prin
defaultciples behind Universal Credit. We can see the Government has made
default significant progress in designing a system to help ease the transition from benefits to work. We recognise the new system will be effective for
default the majority of claimants but have concerns about some of the more vulnerable benefit claimants. We therefore welcome the opportunity to submit a response to the select committee.
default&#xa0;
defaultOver the next three years 70% of our residents will face significant chang
defaultes to their income. They’ll be managing increasingly tight budgets and we anticipate an impact on both the cost of rent collection and the amount of arrears.
