defaultRecommendationsdefault&#xa0;defaultWe reiterate that we agree in principle the aim of welfare reform /universal credit /direct payments – The 
defaultunintended consequence of direct payments is likely to be higher costs to housing providers, negative impact on credit ratings and fewer new homes bu
defaultilt, as mentioned above. 
default&#xa0;
defaultIf we and other providers are unable to continue to secure temporary accommodation, Local Authorities will have to use Bed and Breakfast accommodation more. This costs more, both to the public purse and in terms of impact on vulnerable homeless families.
